By using Acumatica Self-Service Portal, you can view all the relevant information about your interactions and perform the relevant activities online. ==Your User Profile== In Self-Service Portal, your personal information is stored, such as your name, organization, email address, phone number, and address. You can view and edit this information any time you need to. You can also view information about your user account and change your password without contacting the portal system administrator. For details, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Your_User_Account|Your User Profile]. ==User Interface== Employees on different positions use different sets of forms in Self-Service Portal to perform their work tasks. You can configure the user interface so that forms you use frequently are at hand. You can configure workspaces in the main menu so that the system displays only frequently used workspaces there. Similarly, you can configure each workspace to which you have access. To the Quick Menu, you can add only forms that you use more often.{br}
For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__mng_Personalizing_Modern_UI|Personalizing the Modern User Interface]. ==Your Company&rsquo;s Account== You can update your address information and contact details, and configure and update your company users&rsquo; access. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Company_account|Your Company's Contact Information].{br}
The Self-Service Portal also gives you the ability to review information on your customer companies and configure access to the Self-Service Portal for the contact persons. ==Finance Overview== You can easily view the information about your account, check your contracts, or print an invoice yourself. Within Self-Service Portal, you can see all historical documents, balances, due dates, payments received, and amounts due. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Finance_Overview|Your Company's Financial Documents]. ==Case Management== The Support module gives you the ability to create new support cases, and retrieve the latest case updates any time you want to. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Case_Management|Case Management]. ==Documentation== You can search the knowledge base to find answers to your questions at any time. The Knowledge Base (KB) wiki contains support references, such as information on specific solutions, frequently asked questions (FAQ), and common troubleshooting issues (and their resolutions).{br}
Also, other wikis may provide a secure location where you can find documents, such as marketing materials, educational materials, company policies, and surveys. ==Online Ordering== You can use the Orders module to browse the catalog with the offered products, place orders, and track order progress online. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__mng_Orders|Managing Online Orders].

In Acumatica Self-Service Portal, you can view and edit your personal and contact details and the details of your user account.{br}
