In the modern user interface of Self-Service Portal, you can specify your personal settings so that the UI better corresponds to your work responsibilities. For a description of the modern user interface, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Modern_UI|Modern Self-Service Portal User Interface].{br}
In this topic, you will read about the ways the user interface can be personalized.{br}{TOC} ==Personal Settings of the Self-Service Portal User Interface== You can personalize the user interface of the system as follows:[anchor|#_6800ae2d-218e-437f-a973-c4bc373e2d94] *Personalize the list of workspaces shown in the main menu. For details, see [[#_e5a1a566-0cb3-492b-967f-b63839ab6319|Personalization of the Workspace List in the Main Menu]. *For each workspace, personalize the list of forms and reports shown in the quick menu. For more information, see [[#_c51a9b52-0101-4695-8864-d53a2d175fc1|Personalization of Quick Menu of a Workspace]. *Change the location and size of the main menu. For details, see [[#_973a0a9b-9c6e-4ec8-b9f8-5bf44e6542a3|Changes to the Location and Size of the Main Menu]. [anchor|#_e5a1a566-0cb3-492b-967f-b63839ab6319] ==Personalization of the Workspace List in the Main Menu== In the modern user interface, the links to forms are organized in workspaces, each of which corresponds to a functional area in the system. The main menu displays menu items corresponding to these workspaces (such as '''Orders'''); you can click any menu item.{br}
You can configure the list of workspaces displayed on the main menu panel by pinning and unpinning workspaces. You can pin to the panel only the workspaces that you use in your work frequently. Other workspaces you can access that are unpinned from the panel are hidden under '''More Items'''. You can pin and unpin the main menu items any time you need to (for example, when your work responsibilities change).{br}
For the steps you perform to pin and unpin a workspace on the main menu panel, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Pin_Unpin_Workspaces|To Pin and Unpin a Workspace on the Main Menu Panel].[anchor|#_c51a9b52-0101-4695-8864-d53a2d175fc1] ==Personalization of Quick Menu of a Workspace== When you click a menu item in the main menu, the system opens the quick menu of the workspace that corresponds to the menu item. You can use this menu to quickly access the forms that you use during your work. You can configure the list of forms in the quick menu for each workspace. We recommend that you display on the quick menu only forms that you use frequently. By clicking the workspace header, you can view the links to all forms of the workspace to which you have access.{br}
For a description of how to configure links to forms in the quick menu, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Configure_Quick_Menu|To Configure the Quick Menu Items].[anchor|#_973a0a9b-9c6e-4ec8-b9f8-5bf44e6542a3] ==Changes to the Location and Size of the Main Menu== By default, the main menu is located on the left side of the screen and is displayed in its maximum size. If you need more space in the working area of the screen (for example, to work with forms more conveniently), you can change the location and size of the main menu panel as follows:[anchor|#_447afe57-f40c-4b1d-9050-6bc0df79b0de] *Collapse the menu panel so that only the icons of menu items are displayed by clicking ([image:Portal/Images/Main_Menu_Collapse_to_Left_Button.png|15px]) in the bottom right corner of the main menu panel. *Collapse the menu panel to a button in the top left corner of the screen by clicking ([image:Portal/Images/Main_Menu_Dots.png|15px]) in the bottom left corner of the main menu panel and selecting '''Collapse to Top'''. *Display only icons on the '''Menu''' button and in titles of the main menu items. To do this, you click '''Menu''' and then click ([image:Portal/Images/Main_Menu_Collapse_to_Left_Button.png|15px]) in the bottom right corner of the main menu panel.
For the procedure that describes how to minimize the menu panel on the screen, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Minimize_Main_Menu_Panel|To Minimize the Main Menu Panel].

