By using the Acumatica Self-Service Portal, you can keep track of your company account. You can view documents associated with all companies and branches that are available for the tenant, only a particular branch, or only a particular company. Also, you can view the statement history and check the outstanding, overdue, and prepayment balances. ==Viewing Documents== By using the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_40_20_00|My Documents] ([~/?ScreenId=SP402000|SP402000]) form, you can do the following:[anchor|#ul_emj_41n_y4] *Check the outstanding and prepayment balances *View documents, such as invoices, credit memos, overdue charges, and prepayments, that are associated with any of the following: all companies and branches that are available for the tenant, only a particular branch, or only a particular company, in accordance with the '''Display Financial Documents''' setting specified on the Portal Preferences (SP800000) form *View and print any document *View and print the outstanding balance *View and print the outstanding balance broken down by days past due
For example, you can review and print an invoice, as described in [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Print_Invoice|To Print an Invoice]. ==Viewing Statements== On the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_40_46_00|My Statements] ([~/?ScreenId=SP404600|SP404600]) form, you can view the statement history and check the documents included in a selected statement.{br}
To open the Customer Statement (AR641500) print form, you need to select the period in which the statements were generated, select the statement, and then click '''Print Statement''' on the form toolbar.

You can add contact persons from your organization. For example, you may add contacts to be used as a backup in case other contacts cannot be reached. For each contact, you create a contact account and enter contact information, such the contact&rsquo;s name, position, and email address. You can edit the contact information whenever you want to.{br}

If required, you can add user account information to the contact account so that the contact could access the portal. The user with an active user account is allowed to access the Self-Service Portal. To prohibit the user access to the Self-Service Portal, you disable the user account.{br}

If employees of your organization who use the Self-Service Portal need to generate documents with the business date in the time zone that differs from the default time zone (which is specified by the portal administrator), you can specify the time zone for each of these employees manually.{br}

For more information on adding contacts, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Adding_new_user|To Add a New Contact].

