Acumatica Self-Service Portal gives you the ability to see the contracts associated with your account and the accounts of your customers, as described in the topics of this section. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_27e50dc5-cea6-4bad-ae45-67013f0f7ef6] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#ul_p2b_tfl_4q] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Contracts|Contracts Overview]
| [anchor|#_ce1794be-1119-4302-9106-30e582867e27] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Viewing_Contracts|To View Contract Details]
|}

row.column:
A contract represents an agreement between a vendor (the provider of a service) and a customer (the consumer of this service)—and possibly a partner (which might be involved as a reseller). {br}

Contracts consist of different combinations of terms and services geared toward the particular needs and capabilities of the organizations involved. For example, a contract may specify that your company will be provided certain services—such as cable TV service, Internet access, or web account hosting—from a vendor during a specified period of time. Other contracts may contain service agreements to maintain and repair a product during the warranty period of the manufacturer or a particular time period. Service contracts often include a number of cases (often called ''tickets'') that may be solved during a warranty period. A case includes the efforts, such as the work time spent on problem resolution and the related phone calls and emails, to resolve a particular issue.{br}

You can view the contracts associated with your company account and the accounts of your partners. For each contract you can check the contract details—including the setup and expiration dates of the contract, the grace period, and the services in the contract—as described in [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Viewing_Contracts|To View Contract Details].
==Related Articles==
*[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Viewing_Contracts|To View Contract Details]

