Acumatica Self-Service Portal gives you the ability to submit new cases online and then track them. In this section, you will find detailed information on managing your cases, from submitting a new case to tracking the case processing and then closing the completed cases. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_f4a9bd11-0e17-4259-886c-b26bb46ec406] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#ul_umy_5fl_4q] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Case_Management|Case Management]
| [anchor|#_2f59cc2d-2337-4dd6-8ddf-f6db945ec22e] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Entering_Cases|To Enter a New Case] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Checking_Case_Details|To View and Edit Case Details] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Close_case|To Close a Case] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Tracking_closed_cases|To Track Closed Cases]
|}

row.column:
''Cases'' (also known as ''tickets'') are used to record your requests, problems, complaints, and other inquiries. By using the case management in Self-Service Portal, you can submit new cases, change the case priority, enter additional information, get updates on the case status by email, check the case yourself for updates, and view responses to the case. ==Case Processing== Typically, each case goes through stages; the status of a case reflects the stage it is in, as described in the following table.[anchor|#table_bjx_3vy_rk] ===Case Processing=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="33%" ! Case Status !width="66%" ! Stage |- | '''New''' | You submit a new case. |- | '''Open''' | We work on your case. |- | '''Pending Customer''' | We await your response. |- | '''Closed''' | We have resolved and closed your case. |} When the case is updated, you get an email notification. Also, you can monitor the case by using the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_20_40_00|Open Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=SP204000|SP204000]) form. ==New Case== When you submit a new case, you enter the following information:[anchor|#ul_w31_mqy_rk] *The case class that defines the default case settings, such as the contract and case attributes. *The contract within which the case is processed. For more information about contracts, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_Contracts|Contracts Overview]. *The case priority, which defines the order of case processing. *The case attributes, which depend on the case class. *The subject and the description of your case. Supply as much relevant information as possible, so that we will be better able to help you. *Any relevant files that you attach to the case. *Any additional notes you provide.
For the detailed procedure, refer to [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Entering_Cases|To Enter a New Case]. ==Case Handling== All cases are processed in the order of their priority. When we start working on the case, we change the case status from '''New''' to '''Open'''.{br}
If we change the case status to '''Pending Customer''', this means that we need your input. For example, we may need you to verify that we have achieved the desired result, or we may need additional information. Check the case for details.{br}
You can monitor the case status, as described in [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Checking_Case_Details|To View and Edit Case Details].{br}
After the case is resolved, you close the case, as described in [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Close_case|To Close a Case]. ==Case Closing== When you close the case, the case status is left as '''Open''' with the reason ''Pending Closure'' because we might need to add information to the case before closing it.{br}
When we finish working on the case, we set the case status to '''Closed'''. Depending on the request, the case can be closed with one of the following reasons:[anchor|#ul_vym_5gt_rk] *''Resolved'': You have approved our decision or reply (depending on the initial request). *''Duplicate'': A similar case exists. *''Canceled'': The case has been canceled by the owner. *''Rejected'': We can&rsquo;t process the case for other reasons—for example, because a third-party product is involved. *''Abandoned'': We were unable to resolve the issue because of a lack of response or requested information from the initial owner.
You can view the details of closed cases, as described in [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Tracking_closed_cases|To Track Closed Cases]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Entering_Cases|To Enter a New Case] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Checking_Case_Details|To View and Edit Case Details] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Close_case|To Close a Case] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Tracking_closed_cases|To Track Closed Cases]

