After you have reviewed the contents of your cart, you can proceed to place the order. 
==Order Placement==
When you proceed to checkout, you can review the order details and the shopping information. {br}

By default, the shipping information is automatically added from your contact information, but you can enter any other location you want. The taxes and the shipping charges are automatically calculated, based on the shipping location, and added to the total cost of the order. {br}

After you confirm your order, the printable form is generated automatically. {br}

For detailed instructions, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Shopping_Make_Order|To Proceed to Checkout]. 
==Recurring Orders==
If you make similar orders regularly, you can copy the contents of an existing order to a new order, as described in [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Shopping_Copy_order|To Copy an Existing Order].

row.column:
After you place an order, you can track the order and the order shipments by using Self-Service Portal. ==Tracking an Order== All the orders placed with your company account are displayed on the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_70_00_03|My Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SP700003|SP700003]) form.{br}
The status of the order reflects the stage of the order processing; contact us to get more information about your company orders. The order may have one of the following statuses:[anchor|#ul_f32_vy4_s4] *''Open'': The order is processed, but shipment has not yet occurred. *''Shipping'': At least one shipment for a sales order is confirmed. Click '''View Shipments''' to view the shipments and their statuses. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Shopping_Track_shipments|To Track Order Shipments]. *''On Hold'': The order processing has been suspended. *''Credit Hold'': Your account balance has exceeded the credit limit. *''Back Order'': A shortage of items is found and processing of the order may take additional time. *''Invoiced'': One invoice has been generated (or multiple invoices have been generated) for at least one of the order shipments. The invoices are available on the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_40_20_00|My Documents] ([~/?ScreenId=SP402000|SP402000]) form. For more information on printing invoices, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Print_Invoice|To Print an Invoice]. *''Completed'': All invoices have been generated for all related shipments. The invoices are available on the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_40_20_00|My Documents] ([~/?ScreenId=SP402000|SP402000]) form. For more information on printing invoices, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Print_Invoice|To Print an Invoice]. *''Canceled'': The order has been canceled. You may have canceled the order yourself, as described in [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Shopping_Cancel_Order|To Cancel an Order]; otherwise, our manager may have canceled it for you; in this case, contact us for additional information.
For details about how to track a particular order, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__How_Shopping_Track_Order|To Track an Order].[anchor|#cancel_order] ==Canceling an Order== You can cancel an order that has not been processed—that is, an order with the ''Open'', ''On Hold'', or ''On Credit Hold'' status. For details, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__how_Shopping_Cancel_Order|To Cancel an Order]. ==Tracking Shipments== You can track the shipments for the orders on the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_70_00_03|My Orders] form. You select the order, and then click '''View Shipments''' to see the shipments associated with the order. {br}
The status of the shipment is changed to one of the following as the shipment is processed:[anchor|#ul_nmw_drm_y4] *''Open'': The shipment is being prepared—that is, items are being picked and packed. *''On Hold'': The processing of the shipment has been temporarily stopped. *''Confirmed'': The shipment has been confirmed as shipped. *''Completed'': The shipment has been delivered and the invoice has been generated for the system.
To print the shipping confirmation, click the shipment number. The shipping confirmation shows the company information (on the top left), the ship-to address of the customer, the required shipping information, and the itemized information about the goods being shipped.

