Every Self-Service Portal screen includes basic elements that users use for navigating the system, viewing and managing data, and performing other basic functions. The following screenshot shows a typical Self-Service Portal screen in the modern user interface with the basic elements that appear on it.[anchor|#_5db60fb6-8b12-4487-9d78-f4869fe46478][anchor|#_56c76638-a0f1-4357-90d3-93e4f113fff7][image:Portal/Images/SP_UIG_New_UI_Basic_Elements.png|popup|Basic elements of the modern UI|450px][anchor|#_e8dcb954-7f53-4a1b-bc45-5daa6b1707ed] #Home button #Search box #Info area #Main menu (displayed as a panel) #Working area {br}{TOC} ==Home Button== When you click the Home button, which has the Acumatica logo on it by default and is located in the top left corner of the Self-Service Portal screen, you are forwarded to the home page of your instance.{br}
If the main menu is minimized the Home button is displayed to the left of the Info area. ==Search Box== By using the '''Search''' box on the top pane of the Self-Service Portal screen, you can search for a text string in menu items, form titles, help topics, files, notes, and ''entities'' created using system forms, such as vendors and cases. Additionally, you can search for a form by its title and ID. For details, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Search|Search in the Modern UI]. ==Info Area== The info area, in the upper-right corner of the Self-Service Portal screen, contains the menus and buttons that you can use to sign out from the system, change the settings of your account, and view the business date. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Info_Area|Info Area in the Modern UI]. ==Main Menu== The main menu in Self-Service Portal contains the links to your favorites and workspaces (menus with links to forms). By default, the main menu is a panel located on the left side of the Self-Service Portal screen. You can minimize the menu so that it is displayed as a button in the top left corner of the screen (instead of the Home button). For details, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Main_Menu|Main Menu in the Modern UI].{br}
When you click a workspace item on the main menu, the workspace menu opens. This menu contains the forms dedicated to a particular functional area. For details, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Workspaces|Workspaces in the Modern UI]. ==Working Area== The working area, which is the large area on the right side of the screen, may display any of the following:[anchor|#ul_ksk_wkk_f3] *Form: Self-Service Portal has forms of multiple types. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_Form_Interface|Form Overview]. *The Welcome dashboard: On this dashboard, usually, you can see introductory information about capabilities of the portal. The dashboard is configured by the organization which hosts Self-Service Portal.

The info area, in the right corner of the top pane on the Self-Service Portal screen in the modern user interface, includes a group of menus and buttons, as shown in the screenshot below. These menus and buttons communicate the status of your user account in the system and provide access to certain settings.[anchor|#_5ffedf59-c6ae-4977-bd5b-73dac16c714c][anchor|#_e0fa32dc-285c-4a57-a08b-571f2a0dcceb][image:Portal/Images/SP_UIG_New_UI_Info_Area.png|popup|Info area|200px][anchor|#ul_vvq_ytb_f3] #Business date and time #Help button #User menu button
You can find more details about these items in the following sections.{br}{TOC}[anchor|#section_t4t_43r_f3] ==Business Date and Time== Business date is used as the default date on Self-Service Portal forms and on documents that you create by using the forms. Business date and time, which you can see in the Info area, is specified in an Acumatica ERP instance to which Self-Service Portal is connected. You cannot change the business date and time on Self-Service Portal. ==Help Button== By clicking the Help button, you can open the Help menu, which overlaps the working area. The content of this menu depends on the item displayed in the working area when you click this button. For a detailed description of Help capabilities in Self-Service Portal, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Help|Help in the Modern UI].[anchor|#section_i3t_q3r_f3] ==User Menu== The User menu button displays your first and last name (last name first, with the names separated by a comma) and the name of the company to which you signed in if multiple companies are configured in your Self-Service Portal instance. The following screenshot shows the items of the User menu.[anchor|#_6041d33e-659c-4009-89c3-6a855ad27ae2][anchor|#_ca8b0487-a9fb-4b56-88c2-fe11ae6aa4ed][image:Portal/Images/SP_UIG_New_UI_User_Menu.png|popup|Items of the User menu|200px]{br}
The User menu includes the following sections:[anchor|#ul_bvf_1jr_f3] #Companies #My Profile #Sign-In
The Companies section of the User menu contains the list of companies to which you can sign in if multiple companies are configured in your Self-Service Portal instance. The company you are currently signed in to is indicated with a check mark. You can switch to a different company by clicking the company name.{br}
The My Profile section contains your user name, your email address, and the '''My Profile''' button, which you click to open the [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_40_80_45|User Profile] ([~/?ScreenId=SP408045|SP408045]) form. For more information about the settings of your profile, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__mng_Your_User_Account|Managing Your User Profile].{br}
The Sign-In section contains the date and time of your last sign-in to the system and the '''Sign Out''' button, which you click to sign out of the system.

The main menu in the modern user interface of Self-Service Portal, shown in the following screenshot, includes the '''Favorites''' menu item, the workspace menu items, the '''More Items''' menu item, the configuration menu, and the Collapse or Expand button.[anchor|#_887c3d97-af2d-4163-9eb7-6ff8ef02245b][anchor|#_001e6c5b-51c4-47a7-8f8e-2b52863bbca3][image:Portal/Images/SP_UIG_New_UI_Main_Menu.png|popup|Main menu|200px][anchor|#_196de2f6-9093-47b2-9bfb-d9987035073e] #'''Favorites''' menu item #Workspace menu items #'''More Items''' menu item #Configuration menu #Collapse or Expand button
You click the '''Favorites''' menu item to view your favorite forms. This menu item appears in the main menu if you have at least one form added to your favorites. You click this item to open the list of your favorites.{br}
You click each of the workspace menu items to view the forms of that workspace, which is a particular functional area. By default, the most commonly used workspaces are represented with menu items on the main menu; you can add workspace menu items to the main menu or remove existing menu items. For details on workspaces, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Workspaces|Workspaces in the Modern UI].{br}
When you click the '''More Items''' menu item, a menu is opened with tiles, grouped by broader functional areas, that represent all of the possible workspaces. You can pin any of these workspaces to the main menu by pointing to the workspace tile and clicking the Pin ([anchor|#_a0e32493-6e0c-455b-b03e-24dbdf0fa630][image:Shared/Images/Workspace_Pin.png|Main menu|15px]) button.{br}
The configuration menu contains commands that you click to configure the location of the main menu and to edit the menu items in the whole system (if you are signed in to an account with the ''Administrator'' role assigned). The menu commands are listed in the following table. [anchor|#_d4c5f5e5-9a37-4362-bd76-2c9075d90108] ===Menu Commands of the Configuration Menu=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Command !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Collapse to Top''' | Collapses the main menu panel and adds the '''Menu''' button in the top left corner of the screen (the Home button with the Acumatica logo is moved to the left of the Info area). When the main menu is collapsed, the work area expands to cover the area where the main menu had been.{br}
This menu command is displayed only when the main menu panel is shown on the left side of the screen. |- | '''Expand to Left''' | Displays the expanded main menu panel on the left side of the screen.{br}
This menu command is displayed only when the main menu is collapsed and the '''Menu''' button is shown in the top left corner of the screen. |- | '''Edit Menu''' | Switches the system to Menu Editing mode. In this mode, authorized users can customize menu items for the whole system. This menu command is displayed only for users with the ''Administrator'' role assigned. {br}
For details, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Menu_Editing_Mode|Menu Editing Mode in the Modern UI]. |} By clicking the Collapse button, you can collapse the main menu panel so that it displays only icons, and by clicking the Expand button, you can expand the panel to the full width. By clicking these buttons, you can change the width of the main menu pane when the menu is in both locations—expanded on the left and collapsed to the top.

In the modern user interface of Self-Service Portal, a workspace is a menu that contains links to the forms of a particular functional area of the product. In the following screenshot, the basic elements of a workspace are shown.[anchor|#_a81829e5-aad0-4506-8e6e-815caedd981c][anchor|#_bd782cc5-53ae-4ba0-a378-ae333980b21e][image:Portal/Images/SP_UIG_Modern_UI_Workspace.png|popup|Workspace elements|350px][anchor|#_70a001a5-1062-4365-9e6e-73069680de9f] #Workspace title bar #Tiles #Category #Links to forms
The system displays the list of forms in a workspace in one of the following views:[anchor|#_f94e6f1e-6df3-41be-8f7e-84dd8e627ca2] *'''Quick Menu''' (default; shown in the screenshot above): In this view, the most commonly used forms are displayed. *'''All Items''': In this view, all forms added to the workspace are displayed.
On the workspace title bar, the system displays the view name. To toggle between these views, you click this title bar.{br}
You can personalize the list of forms displayed in the quick menu of a workspace for you (that is, your user account) when you switch to '''Configuration''' mode. The changes you make affect the current user session and all future sessions. For details, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__mng_Personalizing_Modern_UI|Personalizing the Modern User Interface].{br}
If your user account is assigned the ''Administrator'' role, you can switch to Menu Editing mode and customize the workspaces and menu items for all users in the system. For details on the user interface elements of Menu Editing mode, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP__con_New_UI_Menu_Editing_Mode|Menu Editing Mode in the Modern UI]. For more information about customizing the menu elements on Self-Service Portal, see '''Customizing the Modern User Interface''' in the Acumatica ERP System Administration Guide.{br}{TOC} ==Workspace Title Bar== In the workspace title bar, you can find the workspace title, the view in which the list of workspace items are displayed ('''Quick Menu''' or '''All Items'''), and workspace title buttons (which are described in the following table).[anchor|#_9a5b995e-73e3-46a0-84cd-483aef5edaa3] ===Workspace Title Bar Buttons=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Button !width="20%" ! Icon !width="60%" ! Description |- | Pin | [anchor|#_86fd9c38-bd1b-4e83-b812-c6990bc5f055][image:Shared/Images/Workspace_TitleBar_Pin.png|Workspace elements|15px] | Pins the workspace to the main menu panel. |- | Unpin | [anchor|#_8c479164-ed6f-4664-8749-d3597ef31894][image:Shared/Images/Workspace_TitleBar_Unpin.png|Workspace elements|15px] | Unpins the workspace from the main menu panel. |- | Workspace Configuration | [anchor|#_32ff391f-7c02-44ba-bb76-701d22e853d1][image:Shared/Images/Workspace_TitleBar_Configure.png|Workspace elements|15px] | Opens the workspace in '''Configuration''' mode. In this mode, you can select the forms that are displayed on the Quick Menu of the workspace. |- | Close Workspace | [anchor|#_9957ee89-0d2e-42bf-89a0-5f2cd6b7273f][image:Shared/Images/UIG_New_UI_Workspace_Close.png|Workspace elements|15px] | Closes the workspace and displays the page opened in the working area. |- | '''Exit''' | | Saves your changes and closes '''Configuration''' mode for the workspace, returning you to the mode in which you were viewing the workspace.{br}
This button appears only if you are viewing a menu in '''Configuration''' mode. |} ==Tiles== A tile is a special button on a workspace that you click to open a form with predefined settings (or, for a data entry form, with most settings blank so you can define a new entity).{br}
Predefined workspaces contain tiles with the most popular actions and forms for the workspace. You can make a tile your favorite by clicking [anchor|#_0bcb7a74-75b3-4707-aff8-efcc4ebe3c67][image:Shared/Images/UIG_Tile_Favorite.png|Workspace elements|15px] in the lower right corner of the tile.{br}
If your user account is assigned the ''Administrator'' role, you can manage the tiles in a workspace for all system users. For details, see '''Customizing the Modern User Interface''' in the Acumatica ERP System Administration Guide. ==Categories== In each workspace, categories are used to group items by type, which makes it easier for users to find needed items. For example, the '''Activities''' category contains forms you can use to create and view cases. The system provides a predefined group of categories.{br}
If your user account is assigned the ''Administrator'' role, you can manage the groups of categories in the system. For more information, '''Customizing the Modern User Interface''' in the Acumatica ERP System Administration Guide. ==Favorite Reports and Forms== In the workspace, you can add a form to your favorites by pointing to the form name and clicking [anchor|#_ff3aedb9-05d5-476a-a048-ea8f70ac9432][image:Shared/Images/UIG_Form_Favorite.png|Workspace elements|15px] to the left of the form name. Forms that you have added to favorites are marked with [anchor|#_2b89c161-512d-4c06-9d90-36dcd98ff641][image:Shared/Images/UIG_Form_Added_to_Favorites.png|Workspace elements|15px].

In the modern user interface of Self-Service Portal, you open Menu Editing mode (see the following screenshot) by clicking the '''Edit Menu''' menu command on the configuration menu of the main menu. The '''Edit Menu''' menu command is available only to a user with the ''Administrator'' or ''Portal Admin'' role. In this mode, you can customize menu items for the whole system. For details, see '''Customizing the Modern User Interface''' in the Acumatica ERP System Administration Guide.[anchor|#_c618d42f-b9ac-40f7-8929-c163cff1b689][anchor|#_45a2ac63-eee3-4dbb-85a5-068e4622c8f8][image:Portal/Images/SP_UIG_New_UI_Menu_Editing_Mode.png|popup|Menu Editing mode|450px]{br}
