The lists of forms, help topics, or wiki articles usually have a tree structure for easy viewing. All forms or topics are grouped into nodes. The node names in the navigation pane are not mapped to any form or help topic; they are used only to organize the forms or topics into a tree.{br}
To open a form, help topic, or wiki article by using the navigation pane, do the following:[anchor|#ol_mgk_j5x_f3] #In the main menu, click the tab, and then click the module (if available). #In the navigation pane, click the node arrow or double-click any closed node to hide or show the forms or topics within the node. #Click a form, help topic, or wiki article name to open the related form or help topic in the right pane.
==Synchronization of the Navigation Pane== If you browse the forms by using the main menu and the navigation pane or if you use other navigation options to open the form, the navigation pane may not show the position of the current form. Click '''Sync Navigation Pane''' on the form title bar to view the position of the current form in the main menu and the navigation pane. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP_Main_menu|Main Menu] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP_Search_Options_and_the_Search_Form|Search] *[HelpRoot_Portal\SP_Form_Interface|Form Overview]

