You can find helpful information in the '''Documentation''' section of the Self-Service Portal. All the articles are organized in wikis. The Self-Service Portal wiki includes the basic information on using the Self-Service Portal, and the other wikis contain other useful information. ==Wiki Overview== Any time you want to, you can refer to the online product documentation supplied with Self-Service Portal. These materials can be found in the '''Documentation''' section of the application.{br}
You can locate a wiki article in one of the following ways:[anchor|#ul_nmd_42w_l3] *''By using standard navigation options'': On the main menu, click '''Documentation''', click a module, and then click an article title in the navigation pane. For more information about using the pane, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_Navigation_Pane|Navigation Pane]. *''By getting the reference article that describes the form you are viewing'': On the form toolbar of the active form, click '''Help'''. *''By searching in wikis'': In the navigation pane, in the '''Search''' box, type a word, part of a word, or a phrase; then click '''Search'''. You will see the search results in the [HelpRoot_Portal\SE_00_00_50|Search Form] form; click an article you want to view. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_Search_Options_and_the_Search_Form|Search].
