The Knowledge Base (KB) wiki is designed to contain support references, such as information on specific solutions, frequently asked questions (FAQ), and common troubleshooting issues and their resolutions. The KB articles are created by our support professionals to ensure that you have access to all useful information. ==Viewing a KB Article== A typical KB article includes the following information:[anchor|#ul_xkq_1gl_wk] *'''Title''': The number and the title of the KB article *'''Category''': The category the article affects *'''Applies to''': The product the article is applied to *'''Last modified''': The date and time of the last modification of the article *'''Views''': The number of times the article has been viewed *'''Rating''': The article rating *The contents of the article: The symptoms, the cause, and the resolution of the problem *'''Related Links''': Optional; links to additional information you might find useful
==Searching for KB Articles== You can browse the wiki by using the navigation pane or search for specific articles. While searching for articles, you can use filters and sorting to get the results more quickly and easily. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Portal\SP_Search_Options_and_the_Search_Form|Search]. ==Rating Articles== You can rate the article you are reading to help us assess the quality of the articles, if available.{br}
